1
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,400
What's going on?

2
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:49,440
Hurry.

3
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,160
Hurry.

4
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:51,880
Hurry.

5
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:52,800
What's going on?

6
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:54,360
High fever, 39.2°C.

7
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:55,000
With chills.

8
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:56,240
Wet rales throughout both lungs.

9
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:57,400
Oxygen saturation 88.

10
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,520
Heart rate 130.

11
00:01:58,760 --> 00:01:59,360
I'm fine.

12
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,760
I'm probably just tired.

13
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,160
Make way, please.

14
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:03,400
Don't run.

15
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,480
Who said I was running?

16
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:05,560
Let go. Don't.

17
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:06,600
You...

18
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,360
Move inside. This place is bad luck.

19
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:09,080
Let go.

20
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:10,720
If I hadn't stopped you, you'd have run off.

21
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:27,480
Good. That's enough. Lie down.

22
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,200
Gallop rhythm.

23
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,520
Not scattered rales.

24
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,800
Basal rales.

25
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,600
Signs of heart failure.

26
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:45,800
Xiaorui.

27
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:47,480
How many days have you felt unwell?

28
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,480
Two or three days, I guess.

29
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:52,520
Not much coughing.

30
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:55,120
No fever either.

31
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,200
Just a little tired.

32
00:02:58,480 --> 00:02:59,280
No strength.

33
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,880
I thought maybe these past two days...

34
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,280
I just hadn't rested well.

35
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,160
Why is everything I face...

36
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:07,800
only suffering?

37
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:10,240
My brother...

38
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:11,800
My dad...

39
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:14,200
And now Xiaorui.

40
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:18,520
Don't worry.

41
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,680
I'll take good care of Xiaorui.

42
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,440
Did you bring him here?

43
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,480
I... I called 120.

44
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,800
How did it get this bad?

45
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,160
Well, he...

46
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,520
He was outside my shop.

47
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,800
He pushed him down, so I...

48
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:51,080
Young man, take a look yourself.

49
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:53,760
How much is this pot?

50
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:54,840
One hundred twenty-eight.

51
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:57,920
Can you make it cheaper?

52
00:03:58,440 --> 00:03:59,160
I can't go any lower.

53
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,800
I'll even deliver it to your door

54
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:01,760
within five kilometers for free.

55
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,080
You really can't lower it?

56
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,800
No, I really can't, young man.

57
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,920
All right, I'll take it.

58
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:10,520
Okay, okay.

59
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:11,480
Hey, don't, buddy.

60
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,480
I've already paid.

61
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:13,160
I'm taking this.

62
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,160
I'm taking it. I'm taking it.

63
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,520
This young man already bought it.

64
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:17,040
Don't. Don't grab it.

65
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,240
I've paid. What are you doing?

66
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:18,760
Young man.

67
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:19,720
Look, I paid first.

68
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:20,480
So it's mine now.

69
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:20,840
No.

70
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,520
I picked it up first.

71
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,720
You said you didn't want it. Don't do this.

72
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:24,800
No. Give it to me.

73
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:25,920
Hey, kid.

74
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:26,680
Why are you snatching it?

75
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,880
My flower, you...

76
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:30,480
Are you okay, young man?

77
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,560
One hundred twenty-eight yuan.

78
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,520
Now it's wasted.

79
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,160
Are you okay, young man?

80
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:34,800
Young man! Young man!

81
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:35,720
What are you doing?

82
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:36,680
You pushed him down.

83
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:37,480
Young man.

84
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:38,720
What are you doing?

85
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,360
Stop pretending. Get up.

86
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,480
I've seen this trick before.

87
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:41,920
Are you okay?

88
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:43,600
Don't leave.

89
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,080
Don't leave.

90
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:45,680
I still have to find another flower.

91
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:46,160
You can't leave.

92
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,480
You knocked him down.

93
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,480
What do you mean, knocked him down?

94
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:49,480
He was fighting me for it.

95
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:50,720
My flower got ruined.

96
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:52,160
Why did you push him?

97
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,400
No, I didn't push him.

98
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,400
When he was wrestling with me,

99
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,160
I just touched him like this.

100
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:55,800
And he fell.

101
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:56,680
Why did you push him?

102
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,240
What are you doing?

103
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:58,000
Why did you push him?

104
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,800
You were wrestling with me.

105
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:00,520
What are you trying to do?

106
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,720
Lin Yi! Lin Yi!

107
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:02,400
Lin Yi!

108
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:03,480
What are you doing?

109
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,480
He's the one who pushed Xiaorui.

110
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,000
That's why Xiaorui got sick.

111
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:09,160
What does that have to do with me?

112
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:10,040
Stop making excuses.

113
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,480
I have surveillance footage here.

114
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,240
Lin Yi.

115
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:13,800
The chest X-ray is out.

116
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:15,760
It is pneumonia.

117
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,280
Then I'll go check on Xiaorui.

118
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,400
Heart failure.

119
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:31,840
Most likely triggered by pneumonia.

120
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,520
Did you hear that?

121
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:35,360
What did I tell you?

122
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,240
Was that because I pushed him?

123
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,520
The kid was already sick.

124
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:38,400
Aren't you trying to scam me?

125
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,880
Isn't this deliberate?

126
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:40,800
Why would he scam you?

127
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,440
Don't get physical.

128
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,200
Why would he scam you?

129
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,480
Why would he scam you?

130
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:45,680
Don't. Don't fight.

131
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,400
What are you trying to do?

132
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:47,680
What's going on?

133
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:48,880
Who called the police?

134
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:50,720
I did, officer.

135
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:51,680
What happened?

136
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,280
I have surveillance footage.

137
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:54,480
It was him.

138
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,520
He took that boy inside

139
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:56,760
and outside my shop...

140
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:57,720
Stop talking nonsense.

141
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,040
All of you, come here.

142
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,160
Don't stand in the doorway.

143
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:08,360
You don't want it anymore?

144
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,160
What kind of person are you?

145
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,080
No, I was first...

146
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,720
Don't do this. I picked it up first.

147
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:12,760
No, why are you fighting me for it?

148
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,480
You're here...

149
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:14,480
Young man.

150
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:15,760
Who's the boy's family?

151
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:17,160
I am.

152
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:19,840
What's his condition now?

153
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:23,600
Heart failure.

154
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:26,520
Pneumonia.

155
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:29,000
Heart failure and pneumonia?

156
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:31,480
Is it serious?

157
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:38,800
Very serious.

158
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,000
He was diagnosed with dilated cardiomyopathy two years ago.

159
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,080
This episode most likely means

160
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:44,680
it's reached the end stage.

161
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,200
His life may be in danger.

162
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:49,760
Officer, this...

163
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:51,160
This can't have anything to do with me.

164
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:51,800
I only...

165
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:52,800
I barely pushed him.

166
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,000
Just a little push.

167
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,760
How could that put his life in danger?

168
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:56,600
He's a doctor.

169
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,760
They can say whatever they want.

170
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:59,400
Now this whole thing...

171
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:00,560
My heart is pounding.

172
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,560
I don't even know what to...

173
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:03,200
Enough. Stop talking for now.

174
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:05,080
Aren't you perfectly fine?

175
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:06,720
Doctor.

176
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:08,160
Let me ask you.

177
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,840
His heart failure and pneumonia...

178
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,840
Do they have a direct link

179
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,480
to their conflict?

180
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:19,680
Not much.

181
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,240
I watched the video too.

182
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,680
They did have physical contact.

183
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,000
But the altercation

184
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:31,280
wasn't very intense.

185
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,160
Xiaorui's pneumonia is quite serious.

186
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:18,480
But once we start antiviral treatment,

187
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,920
he should recover quickly.

188
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,480
But the heart failure...

189
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,600
We may need to consider a heart transplant.

190
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,720
It's all my fault.

191
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,720
He'd been unwell for days,

192
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,160
and I didn't notice at all.

193
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,400
This isn't your fault.

194
00:08:36,560 --> 00:08:37,720
I've reviewed

195
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,520
Xiaorui's test results too.

196
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:40,400
His condition had been stable.

197
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,240
Who could have expected this?

198
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,160
Don't overthink it for now.

199
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,400
Xiaorui is still young.

200
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:51,840
He's in good physical shape.

201
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,160
Maybe...

202
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,680
Xiaorui will be fine.

203
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,600
Xiaorui will be fine.

204
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:06,200
Right?

205
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,560
Let's treat the pneumonia first.

206
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,720
Then we'll think of other options.

207
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,240
But you may want to consider

208
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:21,400
getting him listed for a donor first.

209
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:34,600
I really didn't start it.

210
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:36,680
I had already scanned the code.

211
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,160
Then he came over

212
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,240
and rushed to pay first.

213
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,560
I know. That shop owner...

214
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,480
Do you think I don't know you?

215
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,160
Don't let him know yet.

216
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,160
Yi.

217
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:57,160
Look at you.

218
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,800
Causing trouble for me again.

219
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,720
Why fight someone over something?

220
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:01,600
Got beaten up, didn't you?

221
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,160
But it's fine.

222
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:04,560
I got revenge for you.

223
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:05,760
I beat him up.

224
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:09,600
Xiaorui.

225
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,280
Now that you're admitted, rest easy.

226
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:12,240
Don't worry too much.

227
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:13,680
The pneumonia should clear up quickly.

228
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:15,760
Xiao Lin.

229
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:17,360
Director.

230
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:18,160
Director Sheng.

231
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,120
This must be Xiaorui.

232
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,520
Yes. My nephew.

233
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,240
This is our department director,

234
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,200
Sheng Nian. Uncle Sheng.

235
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:26,280
Hello.

236
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:27,400
Uncle Sheng.

237
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:28,160
Lie still. Don't move.

238
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:43,680
Xiaorui.

239
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:44,920
Don't worry.

240
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:45,880
You have your uncle here,

241
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,480
and so many experts and directors.

242
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:48,680
You'll get better very soon.

243
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:52,200
Director Zhou.

244
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,360
We'll have to trouble your sister department.

245
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:55,480
Director Sheng, please don't say that.

246
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:56,680
We're all on the same team.

247
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:58,720
Xiao Lin.

248
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:00,360
If you need anything,

249
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:01,520
contact me anytime.

250
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:03,800
Thank you, Director.

251
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,240
Get some rest.

252
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,280
I'll get back to work.

253
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,360
Thank you, Uncle Sheng.

254
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:16,160
Look at you.

255
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:17,520
No one in this whole hospital

256
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,800
gets such VIP care when admitted.

257
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,800
Two department directors from the Heart Center

258
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:21,840
came to see you in person.

259
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:24,480
Now you know whose connections helped, right?

260
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,040
Of course it's...

261
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:30,160
Sister Xiaoran's connections.

262
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:33,800
You're not wrong.

263
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:58,480
Cardiac stem cell therapy.

264
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,080
Cardiac stem cell therapy.

265
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,760
Prospects for cardiac regeneration.

266
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:13,280
Xinghua.

267
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:24,560
Director Jin.

268
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:25,560
Sorry.

269
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:26,480
Sorry to bother you so late.

270
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:33,800
I have a patient here.

271
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:34,520
Twenty years old.

272
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:37,680
NYHA class III, close to class IV.

273
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:40,160
Senior, it's Xiaofeng.

274
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,480
Yes. Long time no see.

275
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:43,520
Sorry.

276
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:44,560
Sorry to bother you so late.

277
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:46,800
Yes, I wanted to ask about something.

278
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,040
I saw that your hospital

279
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,520
has a stem cell therapy project.

280
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,480
We need to apply for ethics review.

281
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,280
Please take a look when you have time.

282
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,680
I'll send you the details later.

283
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,360
Sister Xiaoran.

284
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:07,800
You're awake?

285
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,760
I haven't fallen asleep yet.

286
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,280
The inflammation in your lungs

287
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:13,360
is already under control.

288
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,480
It's nothing serious.

289
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,160
Don't worry.

290
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,200
The school flower-arranging club

291
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,600
has an event next week.

292
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,000
I'm the vice president.

293
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:26,600
I can't miss it.

294
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:29,200
Rest well these next two days.

295
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,800
Once the lung problem

296
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:32,000
is fully resolved,

297
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:34,000
we'll transfer you to a regular ward for observation.

298
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:35,760
Then you can be discharged soon.

299
00:13:59,040 --> 00:13:59,760
Good morning, Director Zhou.

300
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:03,600
Xiaoran.

301
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:05,200
Bro.

302
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:06,000
How is he?

303
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:09,080
I watched over him all night.

304
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,280
Xiaorui's lung condition

305
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,160
has improved significantly.

306
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:16,880
Where's Lin Yi?

307
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,720
He has surgery today.

308
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:19,720
I finally managed to talk him

309
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:21,080
into lying down for two hours.

310
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:31,080
Morning.

311
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:50,000
I thought of a possibility.

312
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:52,840
Stem cell therapy.

313
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,680
I've heard of it before.

314
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:06,600
But domestically,

315
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:07,920
there aren't any hospitals

316
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,360
licensed for clinical use yet, right?

317
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,600
And whether it works

318
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:14,200
is still controversial.

319
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:16,680
There is one hospital in Hainan

320
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,160
that just received

321
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:19,360
a national registered research project.

322
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:21,560
They have clinical trial qualifications.

323
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:23,280
I confirmed it last night too.

324
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:24,280
Xiaorui's condition

325
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:25,160
meets their requirements.

326
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:26,360
He can participate

327
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,160
as a trial subject.

328
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,200
That's great. It's worth trying.

329
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:38,520
Even if it can't reverse it,

330
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:40,800
delaying the disease is good too.

331
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:49,160
As for the donor,

332
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,120
I've already submitted Xiaorui's information

333
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:54,680
to the ethics committee.

334
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:56,840
After their review,

335
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:58,760
we should have a result in the next few days.

336
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,160
Let's go. Shift handover.

337
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:16,480
Perfect timing.

338
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,160
Let's go.

339
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,560
This new

340
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:28,800
left ventricular assist device

341
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:30,440
is only 50 millimeters in diameter

342
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:32,600
and weighs under 180 grams.

343
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:33,480
Its smaller size

344
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,680
allows patients to receive

345
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:35,880
life support

346
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:38,480
while maintaining a better quality of life

347
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:39,800
and better treatment compliance,

348
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:40,920
helping patients

349
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:42,160
return safely to everyday life.

350
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,800
All right. That's it

351
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,400
for today's product training.

352
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:46,800
Ask me if you have any questions.

353
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:50,520
Mr. Qin.

354
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:54,720
Dongli Cardiology

355
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,200
recently ordered quite a few balloons.

356
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:58,760
We've reached a temporary understanding

357
00:16:58,800 --> 00:16:59,760
and made some headway.

358
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:02,360
Since there's a new product,

359
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:03,800
I want to take the opportunity

360
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:05,160
to break into Dongli Cardiac Surgery.

361
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:10,280
Sheng Nian has been department director for eight years.

362
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:12,080
He's a seasoned old hand.

363
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,160
He's not easier to deal with than Zhou Xiaofeng.

364
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:15,560
The sales reps before you

365
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:17,200
all came back defeated.

366
00:17:18,360 --> 00:17:19,480
If you want to break into Cardiac Surgery,

367
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:21,080
you need to be mentally prepared.

368
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,200
I am prepared.

369
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:25,040
I have my own plan.

370
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,240
But when I need your help,

371
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,080
don't leave me hanging.

372
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:32,840
How could I?

373
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:33,440
All right, then.

374
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:34,480
Thank you in advance.

375
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:44,920
No need to worry too much.

376
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,560
All indicators are fairly normal.

377
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,360
Come back for a follow-up in six months.

378
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:49,800
Thank you, Director Sheng.

379
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:50,400
You're welcome.

380
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:51,800
Hello, Director Sheng.

381
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:53,800
I'm a sales representative from Mai'anpei,

382
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:54,480
Ouyang Da.

383
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:55,720
I called you before.

384
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:56,480
Sorry,

385
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:57,440
I'm a little busy right now.

386
00:17:57,840 --> 00:17:58,480
I know you're busy.

387
00:17:58,800 --> 00:17:59,280
How about this?

388
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,440
I'll walk with you, okay?

389
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:01,840
It will only take a few minutes.

390
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,680
We already have suppliers for our products.

391
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,480
Clinical demand is only so much.

392
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,560
We don't have any extra needs at the moment.

393
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:10,000
I understand all of that.

394
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,160
And I know you're busy.

395
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:13,160
This unannounced visit

396
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:14,040
was actually because

397
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:15,000
President Wang Zhifeng from Third Hospital

398
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:16,360
gave me your contact.

399
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:18,480
Speaking of which,

400
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:20,160
President Wang is my mentor's senior.

401
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,440
I graduated from Medical University.

402
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,760
His junior, Jiang Wei,

403
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:23,560
was my supervisor.

404
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,480
I have a meeting at the administration office.

405
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:26,480
I have ten minutes.

406
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:27,680
Let's talk in my office.

407
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:34,840
Close the door.

408
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:44,680
Director Sheng.

409
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,160
I didn't know what kind of tea you like,

410
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:47,480
so I brought you a tin

411
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:48,560
of this year's pre-Qingming tea.

412
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:49,560
The taste is very fresh.

413
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:50,600
You're always busy.

414
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,240
When you have a moment,

415
00:18:52,280 --> 00:18:53,160
it's nice and refreshing.

416
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:55,480
This is the next-generation

417
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,560
left ventricular assist product our company represents.

418
00:18:58,480 --> 00:18:59,280
I'm sure you've heard of it.

419
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:01,040
Their products are top-notch.

420
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:02,200
The policy environment is favorable this year too.

421
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:03,360
To show our sincerity,

422
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:04,400
before I came out,

423
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,680
I applied to the company

424
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:06,800
for some extra support.

425
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,440
You can take a look.

426
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,000
Director Sheng, I'll leave you to it.

427
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,160
I'll visit another day.

428
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:38,040
Director Zhou.

429
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:39,920
I'll get going.

430
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,440
Director Zhou, the meeting's starting.

431
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,480
I believe everyone here

432
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,240
has encountered similar situations.

433
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,200
Many patients

434
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:53,280
still don't understand

435
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:54,200
our cardiac departments well enough.

436
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:56,160
They feel unwell,

437
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:57,200
but don't know

438
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:58,480
whether they should see Cardiology

439
00:19:58,480 --> 00:19:59,240
or Cardiac Surgery.

440
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,400
So they have to run back and forth

441
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,480
between the two departments.

442
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:04,240
It wastes time,

443
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:06,160
and can easily delay treatment.

444
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:07,280
So I want to help them

445
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:08,160
solve this problem

446
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:11,080
and get it right from the start.

447
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:12,680
That's why I'm proposing

448
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:14,240
a joint outpatient clinic.

449
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:15,440
Thank you.

450
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,280
This problem...

451
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:20,800
Wouldn't strengthening triage desk training

452
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:21,680
solve it?

453
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:23,400
Why make such a big fuss?

454
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,240
Triage is only one part of it.

455
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:26,840
In the actual

456
00:20:26,840 --> 00:20:27,840
diagnosis and treatment process,

457
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:28,840
our two departments

458
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:30,120
still overlap

459
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:30,840
in many areas.

460
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:33,440
For example, common triple-vessel disease.

461
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:35,480
Should we do PCI, bypass surgery,

462
00:20:35,720 --> 00:20:36,720
or a hybrid procedure?

463
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:37,760
Both departments need

464
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:38,760
to evaluate together

465
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:40,800
before we can provide patients

466
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,160
with the most accurate and suitable plan.

467
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:45,760
Director Zhou's idea is good.

468
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,800
He's thinking from the patient's perspective

469
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,440
and putting himself in their shoes.

470
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:50,760
But personally,

471
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:51,840
I do have some concerns.

472
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:53,600
First, administratively,

473
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:55,520
when patients come through the joint clinic,

474
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:57,120
which department do they belong to?

475
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:59,480
How do we divide responsibility and performance?

476
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:00,400
Second,

477
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:02,000
our Cardiac Surgery department

478
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:03,480
already has a very heavy workload.

479
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,480
We often have emergency surgeries too.

480
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,040
I'm afraid time-wise,

481
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:08,600
we won't be able to cooperate well.

482
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:10,440
True.

483
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:11,920
Director Sheng makes a good point.

484
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:13,280
But any new plan,

485
00:21:13,360 --> 00:21:14,000
when implemented,

486
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,480
will encounter certain

487
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:16,560
practical difficulties.

488
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:17,560
I believe

489
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:18,520
if the two departments

490
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:19,920
can communicate fully,

491
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,400
many details

492
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,400
can be further adjusted

493
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:24,160
and optimized.

494
00:21:26,480 --> 00:21:27,840
And frankly, Director Sheng,

495
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:29,440
Cardiology already has

496
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:30,360
an upstream advantage.

497
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:31,480
Many patients who need

498
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:32,480
surgical treatment

499
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:34,200
first come to Cardiology.

500
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:36,280
If we set up a joint clinic,

501
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:38,360
patients can receive

502
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,200
surgical input earlier.

503
00:21:40,080 --> 00:21:40,800
In that case,

504
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:42,400
for both patients and Cardiac Surgery,

505
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,120
there's no downside.

506
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:54,160
The heart team model

507
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:55,680
has always been

508
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:56,840
a hallmark of Dongli Heart Center.

509
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:58,920
If cooperation between the two departments

510
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,240
stays limited to internal

511
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,160
individual cases

512
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:03,040
and isn't opened to patients externally,

513
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:04,480
that would be a real shame.

514
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:05,600
Also, the elite team

515
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:07,000
that President Cui asked Lin Yi and me

516
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:08,080
to form before

517
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:10,080
achieved very good results.

518
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:11,520
It helped many patients

519
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:12,920
and greatly improved

520
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:13,880
our Heart Center's

521
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:14,800
disciplinary competitiveness.

522
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:16,480
That's why I believe this model

523
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:17,720
can be replicated

524
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:19,120
and expanded.

525
00:22:19,760 --> 00:22:20,400
Indeed.

526
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:22,000
Innovation requires

527
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,280
the courage to take risks and act.

528
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:24,800
I actually think

529
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:26,400
it's worth a try.

530
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:29,240
It's all for the patients.

531
00:22:29,560 --> 00:22:30,360
And Director Zhou

532
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:31,800
has done so much preparation.

533
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:32,920
Our Cardiac Surgery department

534
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:34,120
will definitely overcome all difficulties

535
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:35,080
and actively cooperate.

536
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:37,400
Thank you, Director Sheng.

537
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:41,360
Good.

538
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:43,480
Let's move on to the next item.

539
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:44,480
Yes, President.

540
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:50,840
Director Sheng.

541
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:53,400
I'll make a detailed

542
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,480
joint clinic scheduling plan later

543
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:55,880
and discuss the details with you.

544
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:21,560
Director Lin.

545
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,120
The ethics review has been approved.

546
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:23,920
Next,

547
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:25,040
we'll arrange for the patient to enter

548
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,120
the organ allocation and sharing

549
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:26,880
system queue.

550
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:34,800
Director.

551
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:36,560
Xiaorui.

552
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:38,400
I'll watch him tonight.

553
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,880
You haven't gone home for two nights.

554
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:43,440
You did two dissection surgeries today

555
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,720
and stood for over ten hours.

556
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:46,240
Go home and rest.

557
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:47,600
You'll sleep better at home.

558
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:49,800
No need.

559
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:53,880
Thank you.

560
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:55,400
All right, Director.

561
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:56,720
Go home early and rest.

562
00:23:56,840 --> 00:23:57,360
Okay.

563
00:23:59,160 --> 00:23:59,680
Liu Dong.

564
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:02,280
Well...

565
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:05,240
I remember last time Haihua Hospital

566
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:06,800
asked you to ask me

567
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:07,480
whether I was willing

568
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,160
to operate there.

569
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:09,880
They asked a few times.

570
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:11,800
Didn't you tell me to turn them down?

571
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:13,800
Yes.

572
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:16,560
I want...

573
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:19,400
I want...

574
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:21,120
Can you ask them again for me?

575
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:22,280
See if they still

576
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:23,080
need anyone now.

577
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:24,880
What's wrong, Director?

578
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:27,160
Nothing. Nothing.

579
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:28,400
Just help me ask around.

580
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:30,480
Okay.

581
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:33,880
That's all. Go on.

582
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:35,480
Is Xiaorui really okay?

583
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:35,840
He's okay.

584
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:24,520
Hello?

585
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:25,680
Director Zhao.

586
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:27,440
Sorry.

587
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:28,160
Sorry to bother you so late.

588
00:25:29,040 --> 00:25:29,800
Are you resting?

589
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:33,480
Little Yunduo just fell asleep.

590
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:37,600
It's nothing. I just wanted...

591
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:38,880
to ask you,

592
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,480
at your hospital,

593
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,520
are you usually busy with surgeries?

594
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:46,560
Mainly because right now,

595
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,720
I'm really quite free at Dongli.

596
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:52,400
So I wanted to ask,

597
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:54,080
if you're too busy,

598
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:55,920
I can come help.

599
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:03,600
I understand.

600
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:05,200
Thank you, Director Zhao.

601
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,720
Please send my regards to the head nurse.

602
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:10,520
Okay, sure.

603
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:27,160
Feng.

604
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:29,600
The infection markers are all down.

605
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,040
Xiaorui is doing great.

606
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,000
He's recovering well.

607
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:34,560
See?

608
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:35,480
I knew it.

609
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:36,680
Our Yi

610
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:37,760
was worried sick.

611
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,600
How many times have I told you?

612
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:42,480
In the hospital, call him Director Lin.

613
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:43,440
Don't call him Yi.

614
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:45,600
Thank you, Feng.

615
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:47,160
Sorry for causing you trouble.

616
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:48,760
This isn't your fault.

617
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:50,560
If you know you're causing trouble,

618
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:51,840
don't fight over flowers again.

619
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:55,480
After you're discharged, remember,

620
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:56,720
don't catch another cold.

621
00:26:57,040 --> 00:26:58,360
The weather keeps changing these days.

622
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:00,440
Try not to go out too much.

623
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:02,400
Did you hear me?

624
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:04,120
If you heard me, answer.

625
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:05,600
I heard you.

626
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:07,240
You sound like a dean of students.

627
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,680
People born in the eighties are so annoying.

628
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:12,800
I was born in the eighties too.

629
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:16,400
Here.

630
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:20,160
Why are you here too?

631
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:21,840
I came to apologize.

632
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:23,560
Well...

633
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:24,480
Brother.

634
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:25,120
Look.

635
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:26,160
Didn't you like this flower?

636
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:27,200
I searched everywhere.

637
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:28,160
They didn't have one in bloom.

638
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:28,440
So I...

639
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:30,080
They had bulbs,

640
00:27:30,480 --> 00:27:31,480
so I planted one for you.

641
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:32,440
I brought it here. Please take it.

642
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:33,760
No need.

643
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:35,120
Right.

644
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:37,200
I'm sorry.

645
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:39,840
It was my fault.

646
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:41,040
I pushed you,

647
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:41,920
and you ended up in the hospital.

648
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:43,160
I was wrong.

649
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:44,720
You have to accept it.

650
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:46,080
Really, no need.

651
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:48,880
Look, I already...

652
00:27:49,040 --> 00:27:50,800
I already brought it here.

653
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:52,760
All right, I'll take it.

654
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:53,920
Yes.

655
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:55,080
You should take it.

656
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:56,160
Otherwise your Sister Xiaomei

657
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:56,920
won't let me go home.

658
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:59,000
So you're relatives, right?

659
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:01,440
My second uncle.

660
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:02,400
Second uncle.

661
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,040
My name is Lu Dadong.

662
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:05,040
You can call me Dong.

663
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:06,760
Or Big Winter Melon.

664
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:07,200
Anything works.

665
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:09,440
I'm Lin Xirui.

666
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:10,920
All right, Brother Xiaorui.

667
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:12,440
Well, get some rest.

668
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:14,160
I'll get going.

669
00:28:14,280 --> 00:28:15,200
Call me if you need anything.

670
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:22,560
Well...

671
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:24,000
Actually...

672
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:24,800
Doctor, since I'm here,

673
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:26,800
I want to ask you something.

674
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:28,000
Lately,

675
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:29,760
I haven't been feeling well.

676
00:28:30,360 --> 00:28:31,520
I'm always short of breath.

677
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:32,760
Sometimes I cough too.

678
00:28:33,080 --> 00:28:34,000
Is something wrong with me?

679
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:37,040
I've seen people mooch food,

680
00:28:37,120 --> 00:28:38,200
but never someone mooch medical care.

681
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:39,360
Well, I...

682
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:41,160
If you have a cough, go see Pulmonology.

683
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:42,240
We treat hearts.

684
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:44,520
My heart doesn't feel right either.

685
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:45,680
Look, before,

686
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:46,520
I could climb six flights of stairs

687
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:48,000
carrying a big fridge

688
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:48,800
without even panting.

689
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:50,080
Now I carry one bag of oranges

690
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:51,160
up to the third floor,

691
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:51,560
and then...

692
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:53,280
my heart pounds like a drum.

693
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:54,160
It feels like it's about to jump

694
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:55,120
out of my throat.

695
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:57,160
How do you sleep?

696
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:58,200
Not well.

697
00:28:58,520 --> 00:28:59,280
I wake up all the time.

698
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:01,400
If I prop my pillow higher,

699
00:29:01,480 --> 00:29:02,280
I feel a bit better.

700
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:03,480
Sit down first.

701
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:04,240
I'll listen to your heart.

702
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:05,160
Okay. Thank you.

703
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:11,920
Cardiology.

704
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:13,600
The heart has internal and surgical departments?

705
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:14,200
Quiet.

706
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:26,480
Have you had your heart checked before?

707
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:27,120
No.

708
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:28,880
Wet rales in the lungs.

709
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,440
Fast heart rate, frequent premature beats.

710
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:31,920
And an ejection murmur.

711
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:37,680
Don't move.

712
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:57,680
Apical impulse displaced down and to the left.

713
00:30:02,840 --> 00:30:03,440
Has anyone in your family

714
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:04,160
had heart disease?

715
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:08,120
My mom.

716
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:10,680
She died when I was very young.

717
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:12,040
Her heart was always bad.

718
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:13,800
And my brother.

719
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:15,920
When he was a teenager,

720
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:16,800
he passed away too.

721
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:18,000
We don't know what disease it was.

722
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:20,920
During morning exercises,

723
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:22,160
he just collapsed and never got up.

724
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:27,920
Is my condition serious?

725
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:29,520
Yes.

726
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:30,480
Your heart needs

727
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:31,360
a thorough examination.

728
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:33,080
Go to the Cardiology outpatient clinic now

729
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:34,080
and find Dr. Zhang Zhen.

730
00:30:34,160 --> 00:30:35,160
I'll ask him to add you in.

731
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:36,800
But aren't you a doctor?

732
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:37,280
You can see me.

733
00:30:37,360 --> 00:30:38,280
Why do I still need to register?

734
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:40,240
Of course you need to register to see a doctor.

735
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:41,680
How else can we order tests?

736
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:43,920
Go on.

737
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:46,880
So I still need tests, right?

738
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:48,720
Fine.

739
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:50,840
Brother, then I'll...

740
00:30:51,520 --> 00:30:52,240
I'll go get checked.

741
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:54,160
I'm off to get checked.

742
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:55,520
It won't be anything serious, right?

743
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:57,240
That way.

744
00:30:58,680 --> 00:30:59,240
To the right.

745
00:31:00,120 --> 00:31:00,720
I...

746
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:07,480
Cardiomyopathy?

747
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:08,720
That's heart disease.

748
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,160
Didn't you just have a cold?

749
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:13,000
I thought it was a cold too.

750
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,720
But the doctor came down

751
00:31:15,120 --> 00:31:15,600
and heard me.

752
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:16,840
He said I had to be admitted first.

753
00:31:17,120 --> 00:31:18,400
Get admitted and have a proper checkup,

754
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:19,080
then see what's going on.

755
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:20,560
I still don't understand it.

756
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:21,240
I'm kind of panicking.

757
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:22,440
My mom and my brother...

758
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:23,840
The doctor also said

759
00:31:24,040 --> 00:31:24,840
it's possible they

760
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:25,880
died of heart disease too.

761
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:26,840
Maybe it's hereditary.

762
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:27,920
The thing is, look.

763
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:28,720
What they've written here

764
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:29,760
sounds terrifying.

765
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:31,000
Now that you're admitted,

766
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:31,600
staying in the hospital

767
00:31:31,800 --> 00:31:32,720
must cost a lot of money.

768
00:31:32,840 --> 00:31:34,160
What are you saying?

769
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:35,200
I'm willing to spend it.

770
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:35,800
I'm willing.

771
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:36,800
No, I'm saying

772
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:37,600
the doctor is scaring you.

773
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:38,760
They're trying to squeeze the money from your pocket.

774
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:39,560
Come on, stop it.

775
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:41,280
You think I can't tell

776
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:42,240
good people from bad?

777
00:31:42,520 --> 00:31:44,080
I've been out in the world

778
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,480
since I was sixteen.

779
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:46,160
Good people or bad,

780
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:47,200
I can tell at a glance.

781
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:48,160
The doctor is a good person.

782
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:49,240
He wouldn't harm me.

783
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:51,680
But this is strange.

784
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:52,440
A couple of days ago,

785
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:53,080
I really couldn't handle it.

786
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:53,800
I was exhausted.

787
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:55,240
I'd get breathless with the slightest movement.

788
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:56,120
But today,

789
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:56,920
today I feel

790
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:57,560
like nothing's wrong at all.

791
00:31:57,880 --> 00:31:58,840
Really. Count for me.

792
00:31:59,160 --> 00:32:00,200
I'll do squats. Watch.

793
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:02,800
Does this look like I'm sick?

794
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:03,760
Three.

795
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:05,080
Xiao... Xiaorui?

796
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:06,800
Brother Xiaorui?

797
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:10,560
You got admitted too?

798
00:32:11,800 --> 00:32:12,920
Come in. Let's chat.

799
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:14,000
Come on, chat with us.

800
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:15,520
Get up.

801
00:32:16,080 --> 00:32:16,880
Let me introduce you.

802
00:32:17,760 --> 00:32:18,440
Brother Xiaorui.

803
00:32:18,800 --> 00:32:20,000
This is Slippery, Slippery's wife,

804
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:21,200
Little Bear, Little Bear's wife.

805
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:22,560
These are all my real brothers.

806
00:32:23,280 --> 00:32:23,680
Oh my.

807
00:32:23,800 --> 00:32:25,880
Sit, sit.

808
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:26,600
Let's chat.

809
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:27,160
Let's chat.

810
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:28,160
Here, brother.

811
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:28,920
Have some oranges.

812
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:30,000
Thank you.

813
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:30,560
No problem. Xiaorui,

814
00:32:30,680 --> 00:32:31,720
you saved my life.

815
00:32:33,080 --> 00:32:34,440
You seem to be recovering well.

816
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:36,240
I'm okay.

817
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:37,520
Let me tell you

818
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:39,040
how Xiaorui and I met.

819
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:39,800
The two of us...

820
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:40,760
we became friends through a fight.

821
00:32:41,400 --> 00:32:42,480
After that fight,

822
00:32:42,480 --> 00:32:43,720
I came to apologize.

823
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:44,880
Then his relatives

824
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:45,720
came over and listened to me.

825
00:32:45,760 --> 00:32:46,840
They said I had to be hospitalized.

826
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:47,520
So I hurried...

827
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:48,680
If not for Brother Xiaorui,

828
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,080
my disease would never have been found.

829
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:50,800
You know?

830
00:32:51,040 --> 00:32:52,800
So from now on,

831
00:32:53,080 --> 00:32:53,920
inside the hospital,

832
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:54,840
I'll listen to you.

833
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:57,280
And out in society, if you run into anything,

834
00:32:57,360 --> 00:32:58,280
anything at all, really,

835
00:32:58,800 --> 00:32:59,160
Sir.

836
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:00,600
I have a stool here.

837
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:01,800
Why are you sitting on his bed?

838
00:33:01,840 --> 00:33:03,080
What are you doing?

839
00:33:03,160 --> 00:33:04,080
It's okay. Sit here.

840
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:04,840
Thank you. Thank you.

841
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:05,600
No problem.

842
00:33:05,760 --> 00:33:06,920
When you're outside, in society,

843
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:08,240
if anything happens,

844
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:09,360
anything at all, just tell us.

845
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:10,000
Brother, brother.

846
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:11,520
See if I don't handle it for you.

847
00:33:12,080 --> 00:33:13,160
Who are those people?

848
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:14,920
Delivery runners.

849
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:16,440
Cardiology patients.

850
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:17,600
There were no beds over there,

851
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:18,840
so they were arranged

852
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:19,840
in Cardiac Surgery.

853
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:20,800
Mei.

854
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:21,800
What?

855
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:23,600
Which elevator did you take up?

856
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:25,680
How would I know which elevator?

857
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:26,680
I don't work here.

858
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:29,680
Sixth floor.

859
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:30,400
We're here. We're here.

860
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:31,800
I need to get off.

861
00:33:32,080 --> 00:33:32,600
Move, move.

862
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:36,760
Bed Two.

863
00:33:37,360 --> 00:33:37,800
I'm here.

864
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:38,880
Why are you yelling?

865
00:33:39,480 --> 00:33:40,000
Coming.

866
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:46,600
Let go.

867
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:47,920
I'm scared.

868
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:50,120
What are you scared of?

869
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:52,040
You're just sick, aren't you?

870
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:53,440
Hospitals exist

871
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:54,520
to treat illness.

872
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:55,680
But the doctor said

873
00:33:55,680 --> 00:33:56,800
mine is kind of serious.

874
00:33:58,040 --> 00:33:59,920
Let go. There are so many people.

875
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:02,520
So what if it's serious?

876
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:05,120
If it's serious, doctors still have ways.

877
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:05,880
We'll just...

878
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:07,800
take medicine when needed,

879
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:09,040
get injections when needed.

880
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:11,280
Don't worry.

881
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:12,520
I'm here.

882
00:34:12,680 --> 00:34:13,560
I'll stay with you.

883
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:15,480
How can you stay with me?

884
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:16,480
You still have to work.

885
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:19,480
Forget it.

886
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:20,720
That lousy foot bath shop closed down.

887
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:22,280
When did that happen?

888
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:24,720
Two or three days ago.

889
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:26,680
I only found out yesterday.

890
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:30,000
That boss promised

891
00:34:30,200 --> 00:34:31,600
a more-work-more-pay bonus,

892
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:33,560
but still hasn't paid it.

893
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:34,920
What can you do?

894
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:36,800
When you ask him, he says he has no money.

895
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:39,200
He's playing dirty?

896
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:40,200
Brothers, let's go.

897
00:34:40,200 --> 00:34:40,680
We'll deal with him together.

898
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:41,160
Sister-in-law,

899
00:34:41,160 --> 00:34:42,080
I'll go smash his electric bike.

900
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:42,800
He won't get away with it.

901
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:43,480
What are you doing?

902
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:43,920
Come back.

903
00:34:44,080 --> 00:34:45,280
What are you doing?

904
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:46,480
Come back, come back.

905
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:47,800
Why do you always act on impulse?

906
00:34:48,200 --> 00:34:49,080
What are you doing?

907
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:49,840
You're going to...

908
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:50,680
Who are you going after?

909
00:34:50,760 --> 00:34:51,480
Fine, fine.

910
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:52,360
Then after I get better,

911
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:52,880
once I'm well,

912
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:54,480
we'll block him.

913
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:55,400
He won't get away.

914
00:34:55,680 --> 00:34:56,400
We'll jam his door lock.

915
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:58,280
Dadong.

916
00:34:58,800 --> 00:34:59,160
Here's the thing.

917
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:01,760
After you get better,

918
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,080
and you're discharged,

919
00:35:03,560 --> 00:35:04,880
I'll go do delivery work with you.

920
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:06,480
I can ride an e-bike anyway.

921
00:35:06,560 --> 00:35:07,040
A girl shouldn't do that kind of work.

922
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:08,000
Why not?

923
00:35:08,120 --> 00:35:08,920
What's wrong with it?

924
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:10,480
You're out in the wind and rain.

925
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:11,840
Why put yourself through that?

926
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:13,440
What job isn't hard?

927
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:14,680
If you want to make money,

928
00:35:14,720 --> 00:35:15,760
what job isn't hard?

929
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:16,400
It's okay.

930
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:21,600
It's my fault for being useless.

931
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:24,000
How about this?

932
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:25,680
After I get better,

933
00:35:26,040 --> 00:35:26,560
and leave the hospital,

934
00:35:27,240 --> 00:35:28,920
I'll work even harder.

935
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:31,520
I'll make big money.

936
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:33,520
Then I'll support you.

937
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,520
You can stay home, watch dramas,

938
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:36,840
eat snacks, and then...

939
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:40,680
I'll order you milk tea.

940
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,120
And get you some chicken feet.

941
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:45,400
There are still people breathing here.

942
00:35:45,920 --> 00:35:46,600
So?

943
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:48,440
If you don't want to breathe, hold it.

944
00:35:49,160 --> 00:35:50,000
I like it. I like hearing it.

945
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:51,400
Little brother,

946
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:52,760
have you ever seen this?

947
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:53,800
So cheesy.

948
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,440
Don't learn this stuff.

949
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,000
Have an orange.

950
00:35:58,560 --> 00:35:59,160
Brother Dong.

951
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:00,480
I...

952
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:01,360
I'll get going first.

953
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:02,160
You rest well.

954
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:03,080
Why, Brother Xiaorui?

955
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:03,280
Don't.

956
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:04,480
I'll walk you out.

957
00:36:04,520 --> 00:36:05,040
No, no.

958
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:06,600
Is he the student you bumped into before?

959
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:07,440
Yes.

960
00:36:07,520 --> 00:36:08,160
Right, I forgot.

961
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:08,840
I forgot to introduce you.

962
00:36:09,080 --> 00:36:09,440
This is...

963
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:10,160
Your Sister Xiaomei.

964
00:36:10,560 --> 00:36:11,040
My girlfriend.

965
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:11,920
Sister Xiaomei.

966
00:36:12,240 --> 00:36:13,920
I'm sorry, Brother Xiaorui.

967
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:15,800
Dadong isn't a bad person.

968
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:16,840
He's just hot-tempered.

969
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:17,800
Don't worry.

970
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:19,160
I scolded him when we got back.

971
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:20,000
I even hit him.

972
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:20,800
Yes, she educated me.

973
00:36:21,160 --> 00:36:21,920
How are you?

974
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:22,920
Are you recovering well?

975
00:36:23,240 --> 00:36:23,800
I'm fine.

976
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:24,520
I'm doing well.

977
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:26,240
Just take good care of Brother Dong.

978
00:36:27,040 --> 00:36:27,480
Okay.

979
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:29,200
Director.

980
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:30,920
Director, the meeting is over?

981
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:32,600
Have Lu Dadong's tests been done?

982
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:33,880
We arranged for an aide all morning

983
00:36:33,920 --> 00:36:34,920
and finished them all.

984
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:36,160
But it's strange.

985
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:37,440
His indicators were clearly

986
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:38,080
so bad yesterday,

987
00:36:38,560 --> 00:36:39,520
yet he still seems energetic.

988
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:40,480
He can't sit still and keeps running around.

989
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:42,120
He's usually out

990
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:43,160
in the wind and rain.

991
00:36:43,440 --> 00:36:44,680
His tolerance is higher than most people's.

992
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:45,560
Keep a close eye on him.

993
00:36:45,720 --> 00:36:46,280
Understood.

994
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:47,480
I kicked once,

995
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:48,600
and the door flew open.

996
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:50,040
My brothers and I

997
00:36:50,480 --> 00:36:51,480
rushed in.

998
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:52,880
Then that guy

999
00:36:52,880 --> 00:36:53,760
was so scared he peed himself.

1000
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:54,200
No way.

1001
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:54,920
He didn't even have time

1002
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:55,680
to put his pants on.

1003
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:56,800
He squatted on the floor, covering his face.

1004
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:57,520
Boss,

1005
00:36:58,120 --> 00:36:58,840
please don't film me.

1006
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:00,120
He was begging me like that.

1007
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:01,680
Did you let him off?

1008
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:02,760
How could I?

1009
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:04,240
I put so much effort

1010
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:05,880
into setting up that trap.

1011
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:07,400
And I remember,

1012
00:37:07,520 --> 00:37:09,480
from his bag to his pockets,

1013
00:37:09,560 --> 00:37:10,760
I didn't leave him a single cent.

1014
00:37:12,880 --> 00:37:15,480
You take pride in something shameful.

1015
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:17,280
Come on, old brother.

1016
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:18,160
You...

1017
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:19,400
Think about it.

1018
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:21,400
If a guy can be conned by a honey trap,

1019
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:22,440
how good can he be?

1020
00:37:22,680 --> 00:37:23,120
Right?

1021
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:23,840
He deserved it.

1022
00:37:24,080 --> 00:37:24,920
You know? This...

1023
00:37:25,920 --> 00:37:27,400
Are you never going to stop?

1024
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:28,560
We're just chatting.

1025
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:32,160
Uncle.

1026
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:33,480
He...

1027
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:35,160
stopped doing that long ago.

1028
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:36,880
The state has reformed him.

1029
00:37:36,880 --> 00:37:37,800
Eat oranges. Eat oranges.

1030
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:39,560
After he came out, he's been living honestly.

1031
00:37:40,240 --> 00:37:42,480
Now he just runs errands and takes orders.

1032
00:37:42,680 --> 00:37:43,800
It's all hard-earned money.

1033
00:37:44,040 --> 00:37:44,520
Sister, have some.

1034
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:45,720
No need. There are... there are some here.

1035
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:47,080
Eat, eat.

1036
00:37:48,560 --> 00:37:49,040
No choice.

1037
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:50,720
Your sister-in-law keeps too tight a leash on me.

1038
00:37:50,920 --> 00:37:52,160
There's a beautiful tiger at home.

1039
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:53,480
As grown men,

1040
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:54,240
we've got to listen a little.

1041
00:37:54,280 --> 00:37:54,800
Right?

1042
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:55,360
Man...

1043
00:37:55,360 --> 00:37:56,600
Look at those thin arms

1044
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:57,280
and thin legs of hers.

1045
00:37:57,440 --> 00:37:58,160
She's strong as hell.

1046
00:37:58,200 --> 00:37:59,240
When she pinches me,

1047
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:00,240
each pinch...

1048
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:00,480
That...

1049
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:01,480
I could hear you yelling

1050
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:02,160
from far away.

1051
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:04,080
Even when you're sick, you can't keep quiet.

1052
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:05,200
Just chatting.

1053
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:06,520
Let's go.

1054
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:08,480
A bed opened up over there.

1055
00:38:08,560 --> 00:38:09,160
Let's change rooms.

1056
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:10,800
Why change?

1057
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:11,600
Isn't this fine?

1058
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:13,920
Move. Move.

1059
00:38:15,200 --> 00:38:16,000
Give me your things.

1060
00:38:16,760 --> 00:38:17,880
You rest. Rest.

1061
00:38:18,120 --> 00:38:18,840
You rest.

1062
00:38:19,040 --> 00:38:20,200
This will be your room from now on.

1063
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:21,920
Okay, okay. Thank you.

1064
00:38:24,080 --> 00:38:25,560
What kind of fate is this between us?

1065
00:38:25,560 --> 00:38:26,160
All right, all right.

1066
00:38:26,160 --> 00:38:27,080
Let me finish.

1067
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:28,400
This is the call bell.

1068
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:29,240
If there's any emergency,

1069
00:38:29,280 --> 00:38:29,800
press it.

1070
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:30,720
The kettle is here.

1071
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:31,840
And the restroom is over there.

1072
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:33,440
I'm your primary nurse, Xiaojing.

1073
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:35,040
Call me anytime if you need anything.

1074
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:35,800
Thank you for your hard work.

1075
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:36,600
You all rest first.

1076
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:37,200
I'll get back to work.

1077
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:38,000
Thank you.

1078
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:40,160
They just told me

1079
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:41,360
there was an empty bed

1080
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:42,480
and asked me to move rooms.

1081
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:44,000
Now we're roommates.

1082
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:44,800
It really is a coincidence.

1083
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:46,080
Living in the same room as you

1084
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:46,720
makes me feel at ease.

1085
00:38:46,920 --> 00:38:47,800
From now on, when Director Lin

1086
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:48,760
comes to see you,

1087
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:49,880
he can check on me too.

1088
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:52,120
Once you're admitted, it's all the same.

1089
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:53,520
Stop talking nonsense.

1090
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:54,760
This is a big hospital.

1091
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,280
Hey, what are you doing?

1092
00:38:59,160 --> 00:38:59,800
Brother Xiaorui.

1093
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:02,120
What are you doing?

1094
00:39:03,120 --> 00:39:04,160
This is my small business.

1095
00:39:04,520 --> 00:39:06,000
I make hair clips and jewelry.

1096
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:07,280
When I have free time,

1097
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:08,600
I sell them at school stalls.

1098
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:10,720
You make them yourself?

1099
00:39:11,440 --> 00:39:12,240
That's amazing.

1100
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:15,360
Look.

1101
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:16,560
They're really well made.

1102
00:39:16,800 --> 00:39:17,400
So delicate.

1103
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:19,600
If Sister Xiaomei likes it,

1104
00:39:19,840 --> 00:39:21,120
I'll give it to you when I finish it.

1105
00:39:23,560 --> 00:39:24,000
This...

1106
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:26,600
How could I accept that?

1107
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:27,080
It's okay.

1108
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:27,800
Thank you.

1109
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:28,520
Let me see.

1110
00:39:29,440 --> 00:39:30,040
This is pretty.

1111
00:39:30,680 --> 00:39:31,280
Really pretty.

1112
00:39:32,600 --> 00:39:33,800
Look at Xiaorui.

1113
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:35,560
So young, yet hardworking and frugal,

1114
00:39:35,720 --> 00:39:36,880
and good at crafts too.

1115
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:38,240
Stop chatting for now.

1116
00:39:38,560 --> 00:39:39,160
Director Zhou is here.

1117
00:39:40,600 --> 00:39:41,480
Let me introduce you.

1118
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:42,160
Director Zhou.

1119
00:39:42,160 --> 00:39:43,200
He's the one who discovered my disease.

1120
00:39:43,240 --> 00:39:44,560
This is my girlfriend, Xiaomei.

1121
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:45,160
Director Zhou.

1122
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:46,240
Hello, Director Zhou.

1123
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:49,160
Sit down and rest.

1124
00:39:53,040 --> 00:39:54,240
Luckily, we found it in time.

1125
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:55,560
Now that you're admitted,

1126
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:56,440
just settle down.

1127
00:39:57,160 --> 00:39:57,920
We'll use medication first

1128
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:58,840
to control your condition.

1129
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:00,080
But we can't rule out

1130
00:40:00,120 --> 00:40:01,480
invasive examinations

1131
00:40:01,520 --> 00:40:02,040
and treatments.

1132
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:03,560
You may even need surgery.

1133
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:06,080
May I ask something personal?

1134
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:08,000
Are you and Xiaomei married?

1135
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:09,200
Not yet.

1136
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:10,160
No.

1137
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:11,920
Do you have any other immediate family?

1138
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:14,280
What's wrong?

1139
00:40:14,680 --> 00:40:16,440
Many tests and surgeries

1140
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:17,840
require a family member's signature.

1141
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:21,480
Can I sign for myself?

1142
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:22,560
Technically, yes.

1143
00:40:23,240 --> 00:40:24,040
But we're worried that

1144
00:40:24,040 --> 00:40:25,120
if an emergency happens

1145
00:40:25,440 --> 00:40:26,920
and you're unconscious and need resuscitation,

1146
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:29,040
it's best to have

1147
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:29,600
a family member present.

1148
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:34,200
I understand.

1149
00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:36,480
Contact them as soon as possible.

1150
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:38,080
Dr. Zhang will write your orders.

1151
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:39,200
Get some rest.

1152
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:42,040
Thank you, Director Zhou.

1153
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:43,520
Don't run around anymore.

1154
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:44,160
I won't.

1155
00:40:47,240 --> 00:40:48,480
Th-thank you.

1156
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:05,120
Sister Yalan.

1157
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:08,520
Bed 12 isn't in his room.

1158
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:09,680
Lu Dadong, right?

1159
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:10,680
How long has he been gone?

1160
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:12,400
He was already gone during my last rounds.

1161
00:41:12,440 --> 00:41:13,400
I just checked again,

1162
00:41:13,400 --> 00:41:13,920
and he's still not there.

1163
00:41:14,120 --> 00:41:15,480
It's been over two, almost three hours.

1164
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:16,920
His things are still there.

1165
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:18,840
Did you call him?

1166
00:41:19,160 --> 00:41:20,520
I did. I called several times.

1167
00:41:20,680 --> 00:41:21,400
He didn't answer.

1168
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:23,240
His family isn't here either.

1169
00:41:23,760 --> 00:41:25,240
I quietly looked around the hospital,

1170
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:26,200
but didn't see a trace of him.

1171
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:28,280
Then we have to report it.

1172
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:29,200
Sister Yalan.

1173
00:41:29,240 --> 00:41:30,240
If the head nurse finds out,

1174
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:31,800
she'll chew me out.

1175
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:35,800
Dr. Zhang.

1176
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:37,440
Lu Dadong from Bed 12...

1177
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:38,360
Did he ask you for leave?

1178
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:39,160
Leave?

1179
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:39,880
No.

1180
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:42,040
He's missing.

1181
00:41:42,240 --> 00:41:43,400
For over two hours now.

1182
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:44,480
Has it been reported?

1183
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:46,080
We were just about to.

1184
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:47,720
Head Nurse Shen isn't back yet.

1185
00:41:48,520 --> 00:41:49,680
You still have to report it to Director Zhou.

1186
00:41:49,920 --> 00:41:50,520
I'll go find him.

1187
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:52,800
The key issue now

1188
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:53,480
is to find the patient quickly.

1189
00:41:53,600 --> 00:41:54,760
If anything happens to him,

1190
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:56,000
none of us can get away from responsibility.

1191
00:41:56,160 --> 00:41:56,600
Yes.

1192
00:41:58,400 --> 00:41:59,160
I'll go look again.

1193
00:41:59,240 --> 00:41:59,800
Go quickly.

1194
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:02,360
Director Zhou.

1195
00:42:05,880 --> 00:42:06,280
Hello?

1196
00:42:06,600 --> 00:42:07,040
Director.

1197
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:07,840
Lu Dadong is missing.

1198
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:09,120
What?

1199
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:10,120
The nurse said

1200
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:10,720
he hasn't been seen

1201
00:42:10,760 --> 00:42:11,480
for two hours.

1202
00:42:13,160 --> 00:42:14,080
Ask Security to pull the surveillance footage.

1203
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:15,200
Notify the Medical Affairs Office.

1204
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:16,360
Send his photo to the group chat.

1205
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:17,040
Any colleagues who are free

1206
00:42:17,040 --> 00:42:17,680
should help look for him.

1207
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:18,480
Yes, Director.

1208
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:30,480
Lu Dadong!

1209
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:35,360
Ma'am.

1210
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:36,560
Have you seen this man?

1211
00:42:41,160 --> 00:42:41,800
Go check over there.

1212
00:42:41,920 --> 00:42:42,440
Okay, okay.

1213
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:45,160
Ma'am.

1214
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:46,240
Have you seen this man?

1215
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:47,000
Hello.

1216
00:42:47,200 --> 00:42:47,680
Excuse me,

1217
00:42:47,680 --> 00:42:48,480
have you seen this man?

1218
00:42:48,680 --> 00:42:49,600
Have you seen this man?

1219
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:52,160
Lu Dadong!

1220
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:53,280
Sorry.

1221
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:57,240
How is it?

1222
00:42:57,480 --> 00:42:58,000
Has he come back?

1223
00:42:58,080 --> 00:42:58,600
No.
